# Copy this file to .env (which is gitignored) before running `docker compose up`.
# Override the defaults for local development.
#
# This lab runs THREE Ignition gateways:
#   local  — your authoring gateway (bind-mounted; you develop here, file-based)
#   test    — runs the IMAGE built by deploy.yml (push to main)
#   production   — runs the IMAGE promoted by release.yml (tag push v*)
#
# Unlike Lab 04, test/production are NOT scanned to deploy — they're redeployed
# by pulling a new image and recreating the container. Day-to-day you use the
# API key against the LOCAL gateway (file-based inner loop / trigger-scan.sh);
# the test/production keys exist so you can verify those gateways over the API.

# ---- Ignition API keys (one per gateway) ---------------------------------
# Leave the IGNITION_API_KEY_* lines EMPTY: scripts/setup.sh (via
# scripts/generate-api-keys.sh) generates a unique key per gateway on first
# run and fills the values in here. The gateway stores only the SHA-256 hash
# of the secret: local gets its token resource via the services/config bind
# mount; test/production get theirs docker-cp'ed into the container after
# every boot/deploy (scripts/install-api-token.sh, run by setup.sh and
# deploy-image.sh — an image deploy recreates the container, and the token is
# deliberately NOT in the image: never bake credentials into a published
# artifact). Nothing key-related is committed — the token paths are
# gitignored AND .dockerignore'd — so every clone gets its own working
# credentials, and this file never holds a real secret.

# ---- Local gateway (http://localhost:8088) ------------------------------
GATEWAY_ADMIN_USERNAME_LOCAL=admin
GATEWAY_ADMIN_PASSWORD_LOCAL=password
IGNITION_API_KEY_LOCAL=

# ---- Test gateway (http://localhost:8089) — deploy.yml target ------------
GATEWAY_ADMIN_USERNAME_TEST=admin
GATEWAY_ADMIN_PASSWORD_TEST=password
IGNITION_API_KEY_TEST=

# ---- Production gateway (http://localhost:8090) — release.yml target ----------
GATEWAY_ADMIN_USERNAME_PRODUCTION=admin
GATEWAY_ADMIN_PASSWORD_PRODUCTION=password
IGNITION_API_KEY_PRODUCTION=

# ---- Image registry (OPTIONAL) ------------------------------------------
# You usually do NOT need to set this. The local scripts (build-image.sh,
# deploy-image.sh) build and run images entirely on your machine with a plain
# local name (cicd-lab-05-ignition) — no registry, no login. And the CI path
# (deploy.yml / release.yml) pushes to YOUR OWN fork's GHCR namespace
# (ghcr.io/<your-fork-owner>/cicd-lab-05-ignition), which it derives from the
# fork automatically — it never reads this value.
#
# Only set this if you want the LOCAL scripts to tag/push to your own registry,
# e.g. to manually push to your fork's GHCR. Use your own lowercase namespace:
#   IGNITION_IMAGE_REPO=ghcr.io/your-github-user/cicd-lab-05-ignition
# (Leave it commented out for the normal, registry-free local workflow.)
# IGNITION_IMAGE_REPO=

# ---- Image overrides consumed by docker-compose.yaml --------------------
# Which image the test/production gateways run. Leave UNSET and they fall back to the
# base Ignition image (an empty gateway) until the first deploy. The deploy
# scripts/workflows set these to a concrete tag and recreate the container.
# IGNITION_TEST_IMAGE=cicd-lab-05-ignition:local
# IGNITION_PRODUCTION_IMAGE=cicd-lab-05-ignition:local

# ---- Shared TimescaleDB sidecar ------------------------------------------
# One Postgres instance, three databases (ignition_local_development, ignition_test,
# ignition_production). These creds are the superuser; create per-env users via
# the gateway DB connection UI if you want isolation.
POSTGRES_USER=ignition
POSTGRES_PASSWORD=ignition
